Trans Nzoia Governor Patrick Khaemba yesterday urged aspirants to conduct peaceful campaigns.&ldquo;I urge my fellow politicians, in whichever party you belong, to conduct yourselves with decorum,&rdquo; he said.&ldquo;We have signed the Code of Conduct. Let us respect it. Those using money to hire goons will not be tolerated,&rdquo; he added. Three days ago, supporters of Endebess MP Robert Pukose and his rival Alwin Sasia clashed, leaving five people hospitalised with serious injuries.The county chief expressed satisfaction with how the IEBC is carrying out the clearance process.&ldquo;We hope that, come August 8, the systems will work even more efficiently. In 2013, the systems failed us terribly,&rdquo; Khaemba said. He spoke in Kitale after he was cleared by the IEBC to seek reelection.